The 2017/2018 festive road fatalities stands at 1 676. That’s according to Transport Minister Joe Maswanganyi who was speaking at a media briefing in Pretoria, where he released roads fatalities statistics. He says the figure is a decrease compared to the previous year’s 1 885 five deaths. Maswanganyi says government will double its efforts to ensure safety on the country’s roads. Transport MECs were present during the Minister’s briefing. About SABC Radio View all posts by SABC Radio